               <head>ʻAqāʼid-i ṣāfīyah by Abū ʻAbd Allah Tirmiz̲ī</head>
               <msContents class="https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85129660">
                  <summary>An extensıve treatıse on the Sufı doctrıne of the existence, nature
							and attributes of God described in the colophon as <title>ʻAqāʼid
								al-ṣāfīyah</title> and attributed (ff. 2r and 2v) to al-Shaykh
							al-ʻārif Abū ʻAbd Allāh Tirmiz̲ī - who cannot, however, be the famous
							9th century mystic <persName xml:lang="ara" key="viaf_39475235">al-Tirmidhī</persName> on account of references to later authors,
							e.g. <persName>Abu al-Qāsim Gurgānī</persName>ī (f. 92r) who died in
							450/1058. The work is not divided into chapters. The author frequently
							quotes sayings of earlier Sufis to illustrate his arguments. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <author xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8350">
                        <persName>Abū ʻAbd Allāh al-Tirmiz̲ī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">ابوعبدالله الترمذی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23259">ʻAqāʼid-i ṣāfīyah </title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23259">عقاید صافیه</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم. الحمد الله الذی ادب
								العلماء بعزیمة خیر البشر و خببهم و سلمهم من الرخصة و المباحات و
								الاشر و سددهم و قومهم فی السراء و الصراء و الباساء. </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">خاتمة الکتب شیخ ابوعبدالله الترمزی رحمة الله
								علیه در باب احوال کمال عقاید صافیه اهل ذوق که ازین منفعت یابند/ تمت
								تمت تم تم.</explicit>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
